comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-14T06:01:27.397Z",claude-code-agent,"Root cause confirmed + core fix landed on branch fix/telemetry-otel-export-nonblocking-health-diagnostics. Reproduced: telemetry on + unreachable OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_TRACES_ENDPOINT made EVERY command (read+mutation) linger ~10.7s (fire-and-forget exportLocalOtelSpan keeping the parent event loop alive on a connecting socket). Fix: refactored exportLocalOtelSpan -> pure buildOtelSpanRequest (no network); finishTelemetryCommand now persists the built OTLP span to a bounded pending-spans queue (runtime/telemetry/otel-spans.jsonl, cap 500, TTL/attempts pruning) and the detached unref'd flush worker POSTs it via new flushPendingOtelSpans, wired through flushTelemetryArtifacts (worker + inline paths). Parent does ZERO telemetry network -> verified 121ms read / 154-169ms mutation with both unreachable AND reachable endpoints; spans delivered + drained by worker (mock OTLP got 2 spans, file emptied). Runtime state now records last_otel_attempt/success/failure + pending_otel_spans."
body: "## Root cause (reproduced 2026-06-14)\nThe prior pm-1byt fix addressed an adjacent timer but the bug persists whenever `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_TRACES_ENDPOINT` (or the base endpoint) is set and unreachable — which is the real dev/prod condition that produced the original exit-13 report.\n\n`finishTelemetryCommand` (src/core/telemetry/runtime.ts:1710) fire-and-forgets the OTEL span export: `void exportLocalOtelSpan(...).catch(()=>{})`. The fetch uses `AbortSignal.timeout(5000)` whose timer is unref'd, but the in-flight connecting socket keeps libuv alive. So although runPmCli resolves quickly, the process cannot exit until the fetch settles.\n\n### Reproduction (sandbox)\n- telemetry on + `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_TRACES_ENDPOINT=http://192.0.2.1:4318/v1/traces` (blackhole)\n- `pm get <id>` (read) AND `pm update <id> --priority high` (mutation) BOTH take ~10.7s, vs 143-165ms with `PM_TELEMETRY_OTEL_DISABLED=1` or `PM_NO_TELEMETRY=1`.\n- Confirms the OTEL trace export is the sole culprit; affects every command, not just mutations.\n\nIn an agent's chained `cmd && cmd && cmd` audit flow this lingering/abort interacts with the top-level await in dist/cli.js and produces the exit-13 / partial-chain behaviour reported in GH-209.\n\n## Fix\nRoute OTEL span export off the parent's critical path into the already-detached, unref'd telemetry flush worker (same model as the event queue): build the OTLP span payload (pure, no network) and persist it to a bounded pending-spans store; the detached flush worker drains + POSTs it. Parent does zero telemetry network I/O -> exits promptly and deterministically. Preserve inline behaviour for tests (shouldFlushInline).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- With an unreachable traces endpoint, read + mutation commands return in <500ms (no ~10s linger, no exit 13).\n- OTEL spans are still delivered when the endpoint is reachable (via the worker).\n- Pending-spans store is bounded (max entries + TTL/retention), atomic-write safe.\n- Full coverage gate green.\n\nFollow-up to [[pm-1byt]]. Related: GH-206 (test-all parent staying alive is the same lingering-fetch symptom)."
